\begin_layout BeginFrame
Survey Papers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Part one of the presentation is based on two survey papers: Blundell and
 MaCurdy (1999) and Keane (2011).
 Blundell and MaCurdy (1999) provides a framework for understanding labor
 supply.
 And Keane (2011) gives the most updated summary of the empirical results
 on the estimation of labor supply elasticities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Estimation of labor supply elasticities is crucial for examining the costs
 and benefits of tax polices and welfare transfers.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Tax policies: federal income taxes, state income taxes, social security
 tax, health and insurance taxes, etc.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Welfare transfers to low income families: Aid to Families with Dependent
 Children (AFDC), Food Stamp Program (FSP), Supplemental Security Income
 (SSI), Housing Assistance, Medicaid, Earned Income Tax Credit (EITC), etc.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
